 A gang of robbers targeted Palazzo Jewellers close-by the mall. Police were worried that the robbers had also targeted Safari Ammunition, and a thorough search was done at its premises. A security officer on patrol drove past the break-in spurring the robbers to open fire on his bakkie. More than 100 rounds were fired at the guard who escaped shaken, but unharmed. • Get your copy of the Middelburg Observer this week for the full story.    Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za